00:00:01,320 --> 00:00:07,720
﻿What happens if you just keep cutting in half?\h

2
00:00:07,720 --> 00:00:12,880
Let’s start with an apple - and\h
a really really sharp knife.\h

3
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:15,440
You take the knife in your\h
hand and, with a flourish,\h\h

4
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:18,594
you slice the apple into two neat pieces.

5
00:00:18,594 --> 00:00:20,280
The apple halves become quarters,\h\h

6
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:22,080
then the quarters become eighths.\h

7
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:26,120
In front of you are smaller and\h
smaller pieces of pulpy white apple-\h

8
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:29,960
But by your fourteenth cut, a\h
regular rectangular pattern emerges,\h

9
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:35,560
And you realise the smooth apple flesh\h
is built out of an array of plant cells.\h

10
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:39,600
You keep on cutting, chopping the\h
cells into smaller and smaller pieces.\h

11
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:45,000
Another eight cuts reduces the cells into\h
complex molecules of carbon, hydrogen and oxygen,\h

12
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:52,187
And with a few more cuts, what was the apple is\h
now ten to the twenty seven individual atoms.\h

13
00:00:52,187 --> 00:00:56,160
And you stop.
Is this it? Can you cut no more?\h

14
00:00:56,160 --> 00:01:01,960
But your knife is incredibly sharp,\h
and you begin to chop into the atom,\h

15
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:06,760
Peeling away the cloud of electrons, and\h
revealing the seeming nothingness within.\h

16
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:11,200
Almost nothingness, for at the\h
centre sits the tiny atomic nucleus,\h

17
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:15,080
A hundred trillion times smaller\h
than the apple you started with.\h

18
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:22,120
But again you are undaunted and continue chopping,\h
the nucleus splits into protons and neutrons,\h

19
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:27,240
Protons and neutrons into quarks and gluons,
and you find yourself in the ethereal world\h\h

20
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:31,800
of the subatomic, a world governed\h
by fuzzy probabilities, the apple\h\h

21
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:39,120
nothing but an ethereal wave upon a sea of fields.
It feels like you have finally reached the limit,\h\h

22
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:50,120
the fundamental pieces of the universe.
Though some think you can keep going.\h

23
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:55,320
After more than a hundred cuts, pointlike quarks\h
and electrons might be revealed to be waving\h

24
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,040
strings,
Barely a trillionth\h\h

25
00:01:57,040 --> 00:02:02,440
of a trillionth of a trillionth of a metre\h
across, vibrating across extra dimensions.\h

26
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:07,680
Down here, maybe even space and time are\h
chunky, fundamental blocks that can be cut no\h

27
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,400
more,
Or maybe any\h\h

28
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:15,880
semblance of reality will melt away, as we find\h
that our universe is truly a simulated cosmos,\h\h

29
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:21,480
churning away on some super-dimensional computer.
Or that our three dimensional existence is\h\h

30
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:26,120
nothing but an illusion, and everything we\h
know and love is shown to be a hologram.\h

31
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:34,040
Or even more strangely, maybe it’s just\h
