1760
02:25:40,080 --> 02:25:44,720
of atoms and molecules seems\h
completely indistinguishable.

1761
02:25:44,720 --> 02:25:50,319
Experience tells us that the atoms are unlikely\h
to spontaneously gather in one corner of the room,\h

1762
02:25:50,319 --> 02:25:53,840
But if we started with all the\h
atoms of air in one corner,\h\h

1763
02:25:53,840 --> 02:25:56,920
they would rapidly spread out and fill the room.\h

1764
02:25:56,920 --> 02:26:01,520
Boltzmann showed that this difference\h
is simply a matter of statistics,\h

1765
02:26:01,520 --> 02:26:07,080
That specific atomic configurations\h
evolve into more general configurations.\h

1766
02:26:07,080 --> 02:26:13,559
This evolution of configurations, from specific\h
to general, is known as the growth of entropy,\h

1767
02:26:13,560 --> 02:26:20,241
And it has become one of the most\h
fundamental rules of the cosmos.\h

1768
02:26:21,840 --> 02:26:24,680
Because these notions of\h
specific to general atomic\h\h

1769
02:26:24,680 --> 02:26:32,200
configurations can be thought of another way,
That order eventually gives way to disorder.

1770
02:26:32,200 --> 02:26:35,439
Let’s try and understand this in terms of energy.

1771
02:26:35,439 --> 02:26:40,719
The total energy in any particular scenario\h
must remain constant - this is another\h\h

1772
02:26:40,720 --> 02:26:45,040
of the rules of thermodynamics,
But not all energy is the same,\h\h

1773
02:26:45,040 --> 02:26:50,319
some of it is useful, and some of it not -
The growth of entropy means that useful\h\h

1774
02:26:50,319 --> 02:26:55,439
energy is degraded into useless energy.

1775
02:26:55,439 --> 02:27:00,040
Imagine you have a cylinder of compressed air.
This scenario is a little like the situation where\h\h

1776
02:27:00,040 --> 02:27:05,519
you have all your air in the corner of the room.
This highly specific case is said to have low\h\h

1777
02:27:05,520 --> 02:27:10,279
entropy as it has lots of useful energy.
And to tap this energy, all you have to\h\h

1778
02:27:10,279 --> 02:27:13,240
do is open the valve.
The rush of air from\h\h

