02:27:13,240 --> 02:27:17,760
the valve can be used to spin a wheel,
And this spinning wheel can be used to do some\h\h

1780
02:27:17,760 --> 02:27:22,920
useful work, such as generate an electric current.
But eventually, when all the pressures have\h\h

1781
02:27:22,920 --> 02:27:26,720
equalized, the rush of air stops,
The wheel stops spinning,\h\h

1782
02:27:26,720 --> 02:27:33,200
and no more useful energy can be extracted.
This is true of every physical process,\h\h

1783
02:27:33,200 --> 02:27:37,960
with useful energy constantly\h
degraded into useless energy.

1784
02:27:37,960 --> 02:27:41,439
Indeed, your body is constantly\h
fighting the growth of entropy,\h

1785
02:27:41,439 --> 02:27:45,799
But to do so, you need a supply of\h
concentrated energy from the food you eat,\h

1786
02:27:45,800 --> 02:27:50,120
Which you process into more useless energy\h
in the form of waste and an infrared glow,\h

1787
02:27:51,200 --> 02:27:57,559
You are doing your part in constantly\h
increasing the entropy of the universe.

1788
02:27:57,560 --> 02:28:02,359
Entropy has been rising since the dawn of time,\h
with useful energy constantly diminishing,\h

1789
02:28:02,359 --> 02:28:06,639
And the question of why the universe\h
was born with extremely low entropy,\h\h

1790
02:28:06,640 --> 02:28:10,240
so lots of useful energy, is unanswered.

1791
02:28:10,240 --> 02:28:16,439
But eventually, in the far distant future, there\h
will be no useful energy left in the cosmos,\h

1792
02:28:16,439 --> 02:28:20,120
And the universe will have entered\h
the state of maximum entropy.

1793
02:28:24,279 --> 02:28:29,319
And so, as we have seen before, it appears\h
that we have reached the end of our story,\h

1794
02:28:29,319 --> 02:28:35,240
For what can happen in this maximum entropy\h
cosmos with no useful energy available?\h

1795
02:28:35,240 --> 02:28:41,240
But remember, the rules of thermodynamics laid\h
out by Boltzmann are statistical in nature,\h

1796
02:28:41,240 --> 02:28:44,559
And in these statistics, bound by probabilities,\h\h

1797
02:28:44,560 --> 02:28:48,399
even the seemingly impossible\h
can eventually happen.

1798
02:28:48,399 --> 02:28:53,040
Perhaps the air in your room could\h
spontaneously gathering into a single corner,\h\h

1799
02:28:53,040 --> 02:28:57,359
or billiard balls could rearrange\h
into their starting formation.

1800
02:28:57,359 --> 02:29:00,639
Boltzmann said that whilst\h
this is highly improbable,\h\h

1801
